TLDR - sftp
============

Overview
--------

sftp stands for "Secure File Transfer Protocol" and does exactly this. It provides encrypted transfers between two machines over a network.

The syntax is wget [option]... [URL]...

Examples
--------

- Open a session:

sftp your_username@remotehost.edu

(type password)

- To get a file and save it to your local machine:

get remoteFile

- To put a file from the local machine into the remote machine:

put localFile

- To copy an entire directory use the -r flag:

put -r localDirectory

- Type *exit* to exit.

